CNN Cuts

In a few weeks, I=E2=80=99m told, CNN C.E.O. Mark Thompson and his digital =
lieutenant, Alex MacCallum, will unveil to the staff their very long-awaite=
d plan to transform the beleaguered 44-year-old global newsroom into a dyna=
mic multiplatform business=E2=80=94one that will ostensibly deepen engageme=
nt among CNN=E2=80=99s large but transient online audience, introduce subsc=
ription offerings, and drive new revenue streams.

Needless to say, it can=E2=80=99t come soon enough. Last week, CNN averaged=
 just 485,000 viewers in primetime (roughly equivalent to the Food Network)=
 and 88,000 in the 25-to-54 demo (exactly equal to the Hallmark Channel). A=
nd while Thompson has long articulated the importance of prioritizing CNN=
=E2=80=99s post-linear future while giving his primetime anchors =E2=80=9Ct=
ime to bed in,=E2=80=9D he no doubt also recognizes that
linear continues to pay the bills=E2=80=94and, presumably, understands that=
 he needs to manage the decline of his television audience in order to buil=
d a runway for growth on streaming and digital.

