x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">In a few weeks, I=
=E2=80=99m told, CNN C.E.O. <b>Mark Thompson</b> and his digital lieutenant=
, <b>Alex MacCallum</b>, will unveil to the staff their <i>very </i>long-aw=
aited plan to transform the beleaguered 44-year-old global newsroom into a =
dynamic multiplatform business=E2=80=94one that will ostensibly deepen enga=
gement among CNN=E2=80=99s large but transient online audience, introduce s=
ubscription offerings, and drive new revenue streams. <br/><br/>Needless to=
 say, it can=E2=80=99t come soon enough. Last week, CNN averaged just 485,0=
00 viewers in primetime (roughly equivalent to the Food Network) and <i>88,=
000</i> in the 25-to-54 demo (<i>exactly </i>equal to the Hallmark Channel)=
=2E And while Thompson has long articul=
ated the importance of prioritizing CN=
N=E2=80=99s post-linear future while giving his primetime anchors =E2=80=9C=
time to bed in,=E2=80=9D he no doubt also recognizes that
linear continues to pay the bills=E2=80=94and, presumably, understands that=
 he needs to manage the decline of his television audience in order to buil=
d a runway for growth on streaming and digital.<br/></td>
